      passage: `<p>The 2021 novel <em>My Heart Is a Chainsaw</em> confirmed that Stephen Graham Jones is one of the most talented writers of horror fiction today. <u>By featuring main characters who are Blackfeet, like Jones himself, the novel also helped to ensure that Indigenous people have a place within the horror genre.</u> But Jones is hardly the only Indigenous voice in horror: Lisa Fuller, a member of the Murri people of Australia, has also written in the genre. Her acclaimed 2019 young adult novel <em>Ghost Bird</em> is set in a Murri community in Queensland, Australia.</p>`,
